In this context, the Cdu should obviously seek alliances and the most probable partner would be the SPD, as conservative leader Friedrich Merz excluded an alliance with Alice Weidel's AfD. The hypothesis of a Cdu/Verdi government remains open, but if the YouGov survey was confirmed, together only 314 seats would arrive, two less than the majority needed to govern.
